title._content: Barstow, Elizabeth of Keene New Hampshire

description._content: TITLE Barstow, Elizabeth of Keene New Hampshire CREATOR French, J.A., and Daniel Sawyer, Keene NH SUBJECT Women - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION Photograph of Elizabeth Fay Blake Barstow, wife of the town minister, Zedekiah Barstow. Zedekiah was born in 1790 in Canterbury CT and died in Keene in 1873. Elizabeth was born in 1792 in Westboro MA and died in Keene in 1869. Dr. Barstow graduated from Yale and Dartmouth and was ordained in 1818. He started the Cheshire Theological Institute and was the last minister settled by the town before the separation of civil and church authority. He officiated until he was 80 years old. Elizabeth was the niece of Eli Whitney the inventor. PUBLISHER Keene Public Library and the Historical Society of Cheshire County DATE DIGITAL 20100421 DATE ORIGINAL 1860-1868?
